  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently with the changes in the spec, when proposing the block the validator client will also be required \r\nto pre-compute the state root when proposing a block. This is how block proposal currently will work according to the spec:\r\n- Proposer runs state transition function without proposer signature validation\r\n- Proposer sets block.state_root to the new state root after state transition\r\n- Proposer signs hash_tree_root(ProposalSignedData(state.slot, BEACON_CHAIN_SHARD_NUMBER, block_without_signature_root)). <- includes new state root\r\n- Broadcast block.\r\n\r\nA PR to resolve this would allow the validator client to perform the above functionality.\r\n",
